#: ../../developer/system/template-implementation.rst:115
#: 057adffdb3884d43a78206990d8da472
msgid ""
"private.img – persistent storage (mounted in /rw) used for /home, /usr/local"
" – in future versions, its use may be extended"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/system/template-implementation.rst:117
#: e3420e6529b843df9925ac9a49408074
msgid ""
"volatile.img – temporary storage, which is discarded after an AppVM restart"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/system/template-implementation.rst:121
#: 542e53e3b0914ed7a8efc453def1721f
msgid "volatile.img is divided into two partitions:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/system/template-implementation.rst:123
#: 43837f0f0405414ab10cc69b5c00d886
msgid "changes to root device"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/system/template-implementation.rst:125
#: f90c129156b5444d94a80affcff15674
msgid "swap partition"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/system/template-implementation.rst:129
#: 6e1fd4d2d5a749b6a8137d5435be36b0
msgid ""
"Inside of an AppVM, the root device is wrapped by the snapshot in the first "
"partition of volatile.img. Therefore, the AppVM can write anything to its "
"filesystem – however, such changes will be discarded after a restart."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/system/template-implementation.rst:132
#: a1b60f265b1d4ddfb6181f101c615111
msgid "StandaloneVM"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/system/template-implementation.rst:135
#: fd56f475b4ad4ee09a4d4d888b6569de
msgid ""
"Standalone VM enables user to modify root filesystem persistently. It can be"
" created using *–standalone* switch to *qvm-create*."
msgstr ""

